result.execSummary:
The defendant Quentin Tyrone Williams was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Quentin Tyrone Williams is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Quentin Tyrone Williams was found guilty of Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
PSI reviewed and corrections made.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.

As to Count 2:
The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 113 DAYS at the House of Corrections with 113 days credit.  This is a time served disposition.

Court ordered the defendant pay all of the following. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment:
All mandatory court costs, fees, and surcharges. Court orders this to be paid by 07/27/2016.


Filed:  
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief
Ineligible Voting Notice & Acknowledgement

Defendant Quentin Tyrone Williams in court with attorney Matthew Adrian Lamke.  Defendant Quentin Tyrone Williams in custody.  Irene Elizabeth Parthum appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Pursuant to plea negotiations and on motion of the State, Court ordered Count 1 dismissed and read-in to case for the purposes of sentencing. 
As to Count 2:
Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.  
Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm.  Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended, and may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored.

Attorney Matthew Adrian Lamke in court, defendant Leamon Hannah not in court, in custody.  Irene Elizabeth Parthum appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Case in court for scheduling conference.  Defense requests plea and sentencing date.  Case remains calendared in Branch 22.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for July 27, 2015 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Quentin Tyrone Williams in court with attorney Matthew Adrian Lamke.  Defendant Quentin Tyrone Williams in custody.  Sara Schroeder for Irene Elizabeth Parthum appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Defendant waived Preliminary Hearing.  Preliminary Hearing Questionnaire and Waiver received and filed.  Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Defendant is advised this case is reassigned to Judge Witkowiak, Branch 22 due to defendant's lower pending case.  Original Information filed.  Copy given to defense counsel who waived reading.  Defendant pleads not guilty.  Scheduling conference scheduled for May 7, 2015 at 01:30 pm.

Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for Electronic Monitoring.  Defendant advised it is a requirement to attend all future court proceedings. Failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.

Defendant Quentin Tyrone Williams in court with attorney Nathan Opland-Dobs.  Defendant Quentin Tyrone Williams in custody.  Carole Manchester appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: tmk.
  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Pocan, Branch 26. Defense moves to dismiss Count 3 for lack of probable cause. Court GRANTS motion to dismiss and orders Count 3 dismissed without prejudice. Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold the defendant for further proceedings. Defense enters plea of NOT GUILTY as to count 2. DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for April 15, 2015 at 01:30 pm.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
